latestPosts.caption:
Plump, Gloss, Slay! ✨💋

The Typsy Beauty Glossified Lip Plumper in K-Pop is a stunning shade between cherry red and deep pink, adding the perfect touch of shine and color. It has a smooth, non-sticky finish, and the minty tingling sensation gives lips a fuller, plumped-up look while keeping them hydrated.

✨ Pros:
✔️ High-shine & comfortable wear
✔️ Hydrating formula
✔️ Beautiful cherry-pink shade for all skin tones
✔️ Noticeable plumping effect with a refreshing minty tingle

⚡ Cons:
➖ Tingling sensation may be strong for some
➖ Not fully opaque, so if you have dual-toned lips, your natural pigmentation may peek through

A glossy lip moment never goes out of style! #TypsyBeauty #Glossified #KPopLips #PlumpAndShine

✨ Glass-like shine, deep hydration & effortless application! ✨ Introducing MyHues HyGlow Lip Elixir in Heer (a perfect nude brown) & Yana (a bold, gorgeous pink) – your lips, but even better!

Quantity: 5ml each

Price: ₹699.00 each (currently on discount)

Pros:
	•	💧 Ultra-hydrating, non-sticky formula
	•	✨ Glass-like glossy finish
	•	🌿 Nourishing ingredients for soft lips
	•	💄 Beautiful everyday shades
	•	🖌 Easy to reapply – no mirror needed!

Cons:
	•	⏳ Needs reapplication after meals
	•	🌟 Glossy finish might not be for matte lovers

Are you team nude brown or team pink? 💖☕ Drop your pick in the comments! ⬇️

#MyHues #HyGlowLipElixir #GlossyLips #HydratedLips #NudeLips #PinkLips #LipOil #GlowingLips #MakeupMustHaves

Skin1004 Madagascar Centella Hyalu-Cica Waterfit Sun Serum -  here’s my take:

Pros:
	•	Lightweight texture that absorbs quickly without feeling very greasy, but leaves a soft, glowy finish 🌟
	•	High SPF 50+ for strong sun protection ☀️
	•	Contains Centella Asiatica and Hyaluronic Acid for soothing and hydration 💧
	•	Leaves the skin smooth and refreshed ✨

Cons:
	•	The scent might be a bit strong for those sensitive to fragrance 🌸
	•	Too heavy for oily skin, especially in hot weather 🌡️
	•	Not hydrating enough to use as a standalone moisturizer for dry skin 🧴
	•	On the pricier side 💸

It’s best as a sunscreen, and if you have oily skin, it can double as both sunscreen and moisturizer. For dry skin, you may need extra hydration underneath.

#Skin1004 #SunSerum #SPF50 #Centella #HyaluronicAcid #SunProtection #GlowySkin #Hydration #OilySkin #SkincareReview #ExpensiveSkincare

latestPosts.caption:
🌞 The Face Shop Vegan Moisturising Sun Serum Review 🌞

I’ve completely emptied the tube of The Face Shop’s Vegan Moisturising Sun Serum, and here’s my experience:

✨ Key Features:
This sun serum uses chemical sunscreen filters to provide broad-spectrum protection against both UVA and UVB rays, while maintaining a lightweight and breathable texture.

💧 Pros:
	•	Moisturising: It delivers excellent hydration, leaving the skin soft and nourished.
	•	Lightweight: The serum absorbs quickly and doesn’t leave a greasy or heavy feeling, making it suitable for most skin types.
	•	Cruelty-Free & Vegan: It’s free from animal-derived ingredients and not tested on animals, making it a great ethical choice.
	•	Gentle: It’s safe for sensitive skin, with no irritation or breakouts.
	•	No White Cast: The formula blends smoothly and doesn’t leave a white residue, making it ideal for deeper skin tones.

⚖️ Cons:
	•	Slightly Oily Finish: It may be a bit too hydrating for those with oily skin, leaving a dewy finish.
	•	Fragrance: The mild fragrance could be a concern for those with fragrance sensitivities.

After finishing the tube, I can confidently say that this sun serum is a great option for anyone looking for a moisturising, vegan sunscreen with effective sun protection. 🌿🌞

🙃This sunscreen is always travelling with me hence it looks very well used!

#TheFaceShop #VeganSunscreen #CrueltyFree #SkincareReview #MoisturisingSunscreen #SunSerum #SkincareEssentials #HealthySkin
latestPosts.alt: Photo by Utkarsha in Mumbai, Maharashtra with @thefaceshopindia_official.

latestPosts.caption:
“Just emptied my tube of IPCA Acne-UV SPF 50, and here’s my honest take. 🌞 Formulated with a blend of physical and chemical filters—including Titanium Dioxide for physical protection and Tinosorb-S and Uvinul A-Plus as new-generation chemical filters—this sunscreen offers broad-spectrum protection (SPF 50 and PA+++) against both UVA and UVB rays. The lightweight, silicone-based formula (featuring Dimethicone) absorbs quickly and leaves a matte finish—perfect under makeup! 🙌

What I love most is that it didn’t cause any breakouts, which is rare for my acne-prone skin. It’s also water-resistant, so it stays put even through a bit of sweat or humidity. The only downside is the slight white cast it leaves initially after applying. While it fades over time, it can be a concern for darker skin tones. But once it settles, it blends in perfectly.

Overall, a solid sunscreen with great protection, just be aware of that initial white cast.

Have you tried this? 

#IPCA #AcneUV #SPF50 #SunscreenReview #AcneProneSkin #SkincareJourney #BeautyCommunity”

latestPosts.caption:
Super effective fits in your pocket and have more than one uses? 

I always have this handy when not at home - it’s the Innisfree no-sebum AC powder. @innisfreeindia

You can see from its condition how much I use this. 

Now how do I use it ? 
- to powder my face when it gets oily/shiny
- I take some powder out and use it as dry shampoo to quickly fix oily hair and bring some bounce into them. I used this a lot during my 2 week trip to Europe last month

I don’t generally use it while doing my makeup and keep this only for travel given its size and function. 

Have you tried this? I believe there is another cheaper variant too - have not tried it maybe after I finish this! I will prefer this over compact only because I can use it as dry shampoo too! 

If you are lucky you can get this during BOGO sales on their website. I am planning to get one for husband too!

It was the lowest price I’ve seen till date on this product and lucky are those who got it! 

June - July is the season of sale so buck up!
